<div id="review_1455111370" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1455111370" />
    <a title="Tony Hynes" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/48966753-tony-hynes"><img alt="Tony Hynes" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447541936p2/48966753.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1455111370?book_show_action=true">Nov 29, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Tony Hynes" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Tony Hynes" href="/user/show/48966753-tony-hynes">Tony Hynes</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1455111370" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5558191919863786767">This is probably my favorite book. It impacted me in ways that are hard to describe. For one, Brown&apos;s account of what happened to those who used heroine stuck with me to this day. I wasn&apos;t exactly thinking about trying heroine or any other hard drug before, but reading Manchild in the Promised Land ensured I would never go down that path. Throughout the book it seems like Claude loses everyone he ever cared about to jail, heroine, or death. If anyone wonders where the anger of the Black Panther </span>
  <span id="freeText5558191919863786767" style="display:none">This is probably my favorite book. It impacted me in ways that are hard to describe. For one, Brown's account of what happened to those who used heroine stuck with me to this day. I wasn't exactly thinking about trying heroine or any other hard drug before, but reading Manchild in the Promised Land ensured I would never go down that path. Throughout the book it seems like Claude loses everyone he ever cared about to jail, heroine, or death. If anyone wonders where the anger of the Black Panther Party came from, they need look no further than this book, which chronicles how difficult it was to grow up in Harlem (and in any inner city really) for a young black male in the 40's,50's,and 60's. I'm not sure I would have handled it with as much class as Brown. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5558191919863786767" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


